Professor Eric Cline says the Bronze Age civilisations were hit by a 'perfect storm' of disasters 3,200 years ago . 
  He says the collapse of the Egyptians, Babylonians and Mycenians was a domino effect . 
  He claims a series of droughts, famines, earthquakes and invasions happened in quick succession between 1225BC and 1177 BC . 
  The collapse of these civilisations was a turning point in history , he says . 
 